Path: godot/tutorials/performance/using_multiple_threads.rst
Summary: This section introduces the concept of threads in Godot for parallel execution and warns about thread safety.
Threads allow simultaneous execution of code, enabling off-loading work from the main thread. Godot provides functions to support thread usage. Note: If using other languages like C# or C++, it may be easier to use their native threading classes. Warning: Before using a built-in class in a thread, check the thread-safe APIs documentation to ensure it can be safely used.
